  "prompt": "What are some songs that make you cry?",
  "response": "There are many songs that evoke strong emotions and can bring on tears for different reasons, whether it's the lyrics, melody, or personal associations. Here are some songs that are often cited as tear-jerkers:\n\n1. **\"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton** - Written after the tragic loss of his son, this song touches on profound grief and longing.\n2. **\"Hallelujah\" by Jeff Buckley (originally by Leonard Cohen)** - The haunting melody and contemplative lyrics can evoke feelings of sadness and reflection.\n3. **\"Fix You\" by Coldplay** - This song speaks to themes of support and healing in times of struggle, touching many listeners deeply.\n4. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele** - Known for its heart-wrenching lyrics about lost love, this ballad resonates with anyone who has experienced heartbreak.\n5. **\"Creep\" by Radiohead** - The feelings of isolation and inadequacy expressed in this song can strike a chord with many listeners.\n6. **\"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron** - This song captures the pain of longing for a moment or a love that has passed.\n7. **\"Everybody Hurts\" by R.E.M.** - An anthem for those going through tough times, reminding listeners they're not alone in their pain.\n8. **\"Breathe Me\" by Sia** - The vulnerability in Sia's delivery and the introspective lyrics touch on themes of despair and longing for connection.\n9. **\"Bridge Over Troubled Water\" by Simon & Garfunkel** - A beautiful expression of support and companionship in difficult times.\n10. **\"My Heart Will Go On\" by Celine Dion** - Known for its connection to \"Titanic,\" this song encapsulates enduring love and loss.\n\nUltimately, which songs make you cry can be very personal and often depends on individual experiences and memories associated with the music.",
